<br>
<br>
Aphrodite is the goddess of love and beauty.  She was born morbidly from the foam (aphro is greek for foam) of the castrated privates of the titian Cronus and the warm sea waters near Cyprus.  Zephyr, the god of the west winds, found her and brought her to Zeus.  Zeus, either amazed by her beauty or just wanted to piss Hera off, immediately made her one the 12 major god of Olympus.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.xenafan.com/gallery/official/thumbnails/aphrodite_01.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
Aphrodite caught the attention of all the gods on Olympus, especially the males.  To keep order on his realm and to halt all the annoying wolf calls, Zeus offered Aphrodite's hand in marriage to Hephaestus, the lame and practical forge god.  However, this didn't stop the lustful goddess from making the rounds to other gods like Hermes, Dionisys and, her all time favorite, Ares.  She had many children from these gods but none from husband (who obviously takes many cold showers). <br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.xenafan.com/gallery/official/thumbnails/ares_aphrodite_01.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
Aphrodite may seem to be the floozy of the gods but don't start reciting all those dumb blonde jokes just yet!  She is very intelligent and resourceful.  She not a goddess you would want on your bad side.  There are many instances in mythos where she seeks revenge, plots deception and is just plain ol' nasty.  Of course, she can also a be a kind and generous goddess as well so long as you flatter the heck out her. I mean, she's not one of the 12 major gods for nothing! <br>
